===Etymology===
From {{etyl|NL.}} {{term|ephemerus}} < {{etyl|grc}} {{term|sc=polytonic|ἐφήμερος|tr=ephēmeros}}, the more common form of {{term|ἐφημέριος|tr=ephemerios|sc=polytonic||of, for, or during the day, living or lasting but for a day, short-lived, temporary}} < {{term|ἐπί|tr=epi|sc=polytonic||on}} + {{term|ἡμέρα|tr=hēmera|sc=polytonic||day}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɛˈfɛ.mə.ɹəl/|/əˈfɛ.mə.ɹəl/}}
* {{audio|en-us-ephemeral.ogg|Audio (US)}}

